 toile, 89,5x116,8cm, The Philadelphia Museum of Art, Philadelphia, Etats-Unis &nbsp; 30:40(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuse ajustant sa bretelle, 1895-1896, n&eacute;gatif sur plaque s&egrave;che Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 31:06(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuse bras tendu, 1895-1896, n&eacute;gatif sur plaque s&egrave;che Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 31:06(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuse ajustant sa bretelle, fusain noire rouge , ND&nbsp; 31:36(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuse ajustant sa bretelle, 1895-1896, n&eacute;gatif sur plaque s&egrave;che Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 31:53(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Quatre danseuses, c.1899, huile sur toile, 151,1x180,2cm, The National Gallery of Art, Washington, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 31:52(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Danseuses bleues, c.1899, pastel, The Pushkin Museum, Moscou, Russie &nbsp; 32:13(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edgar Degas, Vue de Saint-Val&eacute;ry-sur-Somme, 1896-1898, huile sur toile, 50,8x61cm, Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 32:45(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Marcelin, &laquo; Monsieur Ingres&raquo;, dans Le Journal amusant, no.36, 06 septembre 1856, p.4, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 33:40(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres, Autoportrait &agrave; l&rsquo;&acirc;ge de 78 ans, 1858, huile sur toile, 62x51cm, Galerie des Offices, Florence, Italie &nbsp; 33:40(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&Eacute;tienne Carjat, Portrait de Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres, photographie, d&eacute;tail, 9x5,5cm, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 33:40(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Eug&egrave;ne Delacroix, Autoportrait dit au gilet vert, 1837, huile sur toile, 65x54,5cm, Mus&eacute;e du Louvre, Paris &nbsp; 34:01(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Nadar, Portrait d\'Eug&egrave;ne Delacroix, c.1857, &eacute;preuve &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, 23x16,3cm, Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 34:01(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Marcelin, &laquo; Monsieur Delacroix&raquo;, dans Le journal amusant, no.36, 06 septembre 1856, p.5, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France, Paris &nbsp; 34:01(4)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `videosonline` (`id`, `title_fr`, `subtitle_fr`, `text_fr`, `texto_secondary_fr`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `image`, `color`, `home_image`, `title`, `subtitle`, `text`, `texto_secondary`, `bio`, `ilustraciones`, `order`) VALUES
(18, 'Photographie et Peinture au XIXe, III', 'Les symbolistes et la photographie', '<p class=\"font_8\"><span class=\"color_14\">Paul Gauguin, Edvard Munch et Fernand Khnopff repr&eacute;sentent, chacun &agrave; leur mani&egrave;re la quintessence d\'un art nomm&eacute; le Symbolisme ; un art de l\'&eacute;vanescence, de l\'invisibilit&eacute; et de l\'int&eacute;riorit&eacute;. Quel peut-&ecirc;tre le r&ocirc;le dans ce contexte de la photographie, elle qui marque un retour si violent au r&eacute;el ?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span class=\"color_14\">​Gauguin collectionne les photographies d\'&oelig;uvres occidentales et plus exotiques ; il se cr&eacute;e une famille artistique qui devait jouer un r&ocirc;le de substitut au r&eacute;el et, paradoxalement, d\'authentification de ses r&ecirc;ves.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span class=\"color_14\">Munch, le peintre des &eacute;tats d\'&acirc;me, du cycle de la vie et de la mort engagea un dialogue permanent entre peintures, photographies et cam&eacute;ra : un parcours &agrave; d&eacute;couvrir.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span class=\"color_14\">Khnopff, qui s&acute;affichait pourtant publiquement contre la reconnaissance du statut artistique de la photographie, cachait un remarquable &eacute;quipement photographique dans son atelier. Faut-il en d&eacute;duire que cet excellent dessinateur trichait en copiant l\'image photographique ? R&eacute;ponse simpliste et limit&eacute;e; son &oelig;uvre m&eacute;rite de plus amples investigations.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\"><span class=\"color_14\">​​Cette troisi&egrave;me conf&eacute;rence sur la relation inavou&eacute;e entre peinture et photographie investit la plus contre-nature des collaborations, &agrave; savoir : comment la photographie, gravure du r&eacute;el, a-t-elle pu &ecirc;tre mise au service de la transcendance de ce m&ecirc;me r&eacute;el ?</span></p>', 'La génération symboliste aspire à élever l\'âme vers une dimension spirituelle. Or cette sublimation passe souvent, bien que discrètement, par une étude de l’image photographique.', '2024-10-12 02:26:00', '2024-10-25 00:11:02', 'videosonline/October2024/7B3tTZIE63HQNfWVvuib.jpg', '#1c3d00', 'videosonline/October2024/I1naOvyuR64AggOudzQm.jpg', 'Photographie et Peinture au XIXe, III', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The Artist and The Camera : Degas to Picasso, catalogue d’exposition, Dallas Museum of Art, 2000\r\n\r\nMunch : L\'Œil moderne, catalogue d\'exposition, Tate Modern, 2012\r\n\r\nArne Eggum, Munch and Photography, Yale University Press,1989', '<div id=\"bgLayers_comp-lo7tnrcc3\" class=\"MW5IWV\" data-hook=\"bgLayers\" data-motion-part=\"BG_LAYER\">\r\n<div id=\"bgMedia_comp-lo7tnrcc3\" class=\"VgO9Yg\" data-motion-part=\"BG_MEDIA\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"\" data-mesh-id=\"comp-lo7tnrcc3inlineContent\" data-testid=\"inline-content\">\r\n<div data-mesh-id=\"comp-lo7tnrcc3inlineContent-gridContainer\" data-testid=\"mesh-container-content\">\r\n<div id=\"comp-lo7tnrcf\" class=\"HcOXKn c9GqVL QxJLC3 lq2cno comp-lo7tnrcf wixui-rich-text\" data-testid=\"richTextElement\">\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Alphonse Mucha, Paul Gauguin jouant l\'harmonium &agrave; l\'atelier d\'Alphonse Mucha, rue de la Grande-Chaumi&egrave;re, Paris, c.1893, photographie, Mus&eacute;e du Luxembourg, Paris, France &nbsp; 2:31(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Henri Lemasson, D&rsquo;o&ugrave; venons nous?, photographie, 1898, ND&nbsp; &nbsp; 5:09(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jules Agostini,&nbsp; &laquo; Habitation du Peintre Gauguin &raquo;, 1896, dans Jules Agostini, Tahiti, planche 80, J. Ed. Andr&eacute;, Paris, 1905, p.70, Biblioth&egrave;que nationale de France &nbsp; 6:00(1) 10:56(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Louis Grelet, Tohotaua, dans Bengt Danielsson, Gauguin in the South Seas, planche 49,&nbsp; 1965, p. 241&nbsp; &nbsp; 12:55(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Manuscrit de Noa Noa, 1893-1901, plume et encre, illustrations en aquarelle, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 13:37(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Dans la vanill&egrave;re, homme et cheval, 1891, huile sur toile de jute, 73x92cm, Solomon R, Guggenheim Museum, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 14:24(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">The Parthenon Sculptures, marbre, British Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; 14:50(1),&nbsp; 16:03(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, &Eacute;tude pour &laquo; L&rsquo;Appel &raquo;, 1902-1903, lieu inconnu&nbsp; &nbsp; 15:44(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, La M&egrave;re de l\'artiste, 1893, huile sur toile, 41x33cm, Staatsgalerie Stuttgart, Stuttgart, Allemagne &nbsp; 16:43(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Portrait d&rsquo;Aline Chazal-Tristan, lithographie, Biblioth&egrave;que Marguerite Durand, Paris, France 16:54(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, &Egrave;ve exotique, c.1890-1894, aquarelle sur papier, 42x8x25,1cm, Pola Museum of Art, Kanagawa, Japon &nbsp; 17:19(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, sc&egrave;ne du L\'Assault of Mara, Frise du Temple de Borobudur, Java, c. 1889, photographie &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 17:37(1), 19:23(1), 26:37(1), &nbsp; 28:45(1), 28:55(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Photographie de l\'Exposition universelle, Palais des arts lib&eacute;raux, Paris Exposition, 1889, impression &agrave; l&rsquo;albumine, Library of Congress, Washington, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; &nbsp;22:17(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Moreau, Palais des arts lib&eacute;raux : Int&eacute;rieur. Paris, Champ de Mars, 1889, photographie, M&eacute;diath&egrave;que de l\'architecture et du patrimoine, Paris</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Le Palais central des colonies, Exposition Universelle, 1889, Paris</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Rez de Chauss&eacute;e du Palais des colonies &agrave; l\'Exposition universelle de 1889 &nbsp; 22:34(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Charles Georges Spitz &laquo; Photographies de Tahiti 1880-1890 &raquo;, dans Jean-Yves Tr&eacute;hin Tahiti, L\'&Eacute;den &agrave; l\'&eacute;preuve de la photographie, Ed. Gallimard, 2003, p.88, 93, 95, 101, 104, Mus&eacute;e de Tahiti et des &Icirc;les, Punaauia, Polyn&eacute;sie Fran&ccedil;aise&nbsp; 22:49(1), 42:44(1)&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Kampong javanais, Exposition universelle de 1889, photographie &nbsp; 23:43(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Souvenir des merveilles de l&rsquo;Exposition de 1889. La danse des mains (Kampong Javanais) &raquo;&nbsp; 23:39(1), 23:50(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Nave Nave Fenua, c.1893-1894, gravure, 39,9x24,9cm, de la s&eacute;rie Noa Noa, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 26:55(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Pays merveilleux ou Te Nave Nave Fenua, 1892, huile sur toile, 91,3x72,1cm, Ohara Museum of Art, Okayama, Japon&nbsp; &nbsp; 26:51(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, &Egrave;ve Tahitienne ou Te nave nave fenua, c.1892, plume et encre brune, lavis d\'encre brune, aquarelle et gouache sur papier v&eacute;lin beige, 29,5x21,8cm, Mus&eacute;e de Grenoble, Grenoble&nbsp; &nbsp; 26:55(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Changement de R&eacute;sidence, 1899, gravure sur papier japonais, 16,7x30,8cm, Brooklyn Museum, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 27:42(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Faa Lheihe (Pastorales tahitiennes), 1898, huile sur toile, 54x169,5cm, Tate Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni &nbsp; 27:46(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Ia Orana Maria, 1891, huile sur toile, 114x89cm, Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 28:32(1)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Idole &agrave; la perle, 1892, statuette en bois de tamanu peint et dor&eacute;, Mus&eacute;e&nbsp; d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 29:04(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Po&egrave;mes barbares, 1896, huile sur toile, 64,8x48,3cm, Harvard Art Museums/Fogg Museum, Cambridge, &Eacute;tats-Unis</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Te atua (Le Dieu), c.1893-1894, gravure, 20,5x35,5cm, de la s&eacute;rie Noa Noa, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 29:25(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Bouddha, c.1895, gravure marron-noire sur papier japonais, National Gallery of Art, Washington, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 29:53(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Idylle &agrave; Tahiti, 1901, huile sur toile, 74,5x94,5cm, Stiftung Sammlung E. G. B&uuml;hrle, Zurich, Suisse&nbsp; 30:57(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Paysage avec trois personnages, 1901, huile sur toile, 78x67cm, collection particuli&egrave;re&nbsp; &nbsp; 30:17(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Charles-Georges Spitz, Danse canaque, Tahiti, c.1894-1900, carte postale version color&eacute;e,&nbsp; 17,8x28,4cm, Collection Dupondt, Art Institute of Chicago, Illinois, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 30:40(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, &ldquo;Vue de la baie de Pape&iuml;te et de l&rsquo;&icirc;lot de la Reine&rdquo;, gravure, dans Magasin pittoresque, 1843</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Le grand Arbre ou Te raau rahi I, 1891, huile sur toile, 74x92,8cm, The Cleveland Museum of Art,&nbsp; Ohio, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 30:50(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Tahiti. Case indig&egrave;ne &raquo;, carte postale, lieu inconnu &nbsp; 30:50(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Manuscrit de Noa Noa, 1893-1901, plume et encre, illustrations en aquarelle, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 34:48(1) &nbsp;