text\">Paul Gauguin, Les Mots du diable ou Para una te Varua, 1892, huile sur toile, 91,7x68,5cm, National Gallery of Art, Washington, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; &nbsp; 37:59(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Manuscrit&nbsp; de Noa Noa, 1893-1901, plume et encre, illustrations en aquarelle, The Museum of Modern Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 38:44(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Paul Gauguin cultural Center &raquo;, photographie&nbsp; &nbsp; 40:17(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Malek Alloula, Le Harem colonial, 1981, pp.62-63&nbsp; &nbsp; 41:55(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Jean Geiser, Une Aim&eacute;e, c.1910, photographie&nbsp; 41:55(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Jardin zoologique. d&rsquo;acclimatation somalis. Chemins de fer de l\'ouest, c.1890, lithographie, Mus&eacute;e Carnavalet, Paris&nbsp; &nbsp; 43:25(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">William-Adolphe Bouguereau, La Naissance de V&eacute;nus, 1879, huile sur toile, 300x218cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris 42:50(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Village de Somalis au Jardin d&rsquo;acclimatation de Paris &raquo;, gravure d\'apr&egrave;s Maurice Bucquet,&nbsp; dans La Nature, 20 septembre 1890 &nbsp; 43:37(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Paris. Les Araucaniens au Jardin d&rsquo;acclimatation &raquo;, La Nature N&deg;531 du 4 aout 1883 1883 &nbsp; 43:37(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">&laquo; Exposition coloniale de Nogent-sur-Marne &raquo; 1907, lieu inconnu 43:44(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Frederick Christian Lewis (attribu&eacute;e &agrave;), Sartjee, the Hottentot Venus, 1810, aquatinte &agrave; l&rsquo;eau forte, 36,1x23,3cm, The British Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; &nbsp; 44:01(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Louis Fran&ccedil;ois Charon (graveur), Les Curieux en extase, ou Les Cordons de souliers, 1815, gravure, 22,2x29,5cm, The British Museum, Londres, Royaume-Uni&nbsp; 44:13(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Louis&nbsp; Ducos du Hauron, Vue d&rsquo;Agen, France, 1877, premi&egrave;re photographie en couleur, lieu inconnu&nbsp; 45:00(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Le Cheval blanc, 1898, huile sur toile, 140x91,5cm, Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris&nbsp; 45:26(1) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, &nbsp;Le Jour de Dieu ou Mahana no atua, 1894, huile sur toile, 66x108cm, Art Institute of Chicago, Chicago, &Eacute;tats-Unis&nbsp; 45:26(1) &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Anonyme, Edvard Munch, photographie, National Library of Norway, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 0:24(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, St&eacute;phane Mallarm&eacute;, 1897, lithographie, 50,6x34,9cm, Museum of Fine Arts, Boston, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 1:53(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Nadar, St&eacute;phane Mallarm&eacute; au ch&acirc;le, 1895, &eacute;preuve au palladium, 19x25cm, collection particuli&egrave;re &nbsp; 2:03(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Paul Gauguin, Portrait de St&eacute;phane Mallarm&eacute;, 1891, gravure, 32,1x24,1cm, The Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, &Eacute;tats-Unis &nbsp; 3:00(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munch, Elisabeth F&ouml;rster-Nietzsche, 1906, huile sur toile, 164x101cm, Munchmuseet, Oslo, Norv&egrave;ge &nbsp; 3:23(2) &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\"><span class=\"wixGuard wixui-rich-text__text\">​</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<li class=\"wixui-rich-text__text\">\r\n<p class=\"font_8 wixui-rich-text__text\">Edvard Munc